[01:03.39]	Sir, by your leave: having come to Padua
[01:06.11]	To gather in some debts, my son Lucentio
[01:08.90]	Made me acquainted with a weighty cause
[01:11.68]	Of love between your daughter and himself:
[01:14.58]	And, for the good report I hear of you
[01:17.24]	And for the love he beareth to your daughter
[01:20.33]	And she to him, to stay him not too long,
[01:23.11]	I am content, in a good father's care,
[01:25.71]	To have him match'd; and if you please to like
[01:28.86]	No worse than I, upon some agreement
[01:31.40]	Me shall you find ready and willing
[01:33.94]	With one consent to have her so bestow'd;
[01:36.78]	For curious I cannot be with you,
[01:39.14]	Signior Baptista, of whom I hear so well.
[01:41.92]BAPTISTA	Sir, pardon me in what I have to say:
[01:44.47]	Your plainness and your shortness please me well.
[01:47.79]	Right true it is, your son Lucentio here
[01:50.57]	Doth love my daughter and she loveth him,
[01:53.42]	Or both dissemble deeply their affections:
[01:56.32]	And therefore, if you say no more than this,
[01:59.29]	That like a father you will deal with him
[02:02.19]	And pass my daughter a sufficient dower,
[02:04.97]	The match is made, and all is done:
[02:07.39]	Your son shall have my daughter with consent.
[02:10.48]TRANIO	I thank you, sir. Where then do you know best
[02:13.50]	We be affied and such assurance ta'en
[02:16.16]	As shall with either part's agreement stand?
